translateText.name: translateText
translateText.label: Translate a Text

expect.help: Text to be translated. Only UTF8-encoded plain text is supported.
expect.name: text
expect.label: Text

expect.help: If this parameter is omitted, the API will attempt to detect the language of the text and translate it.
expect.name: source_lang
expect.label: Source Language

expect.help: Sets whether the translation engine should first split the input into sentences. When sending one sentence per text parameter, it is advisable to set `split_sentences=0`, in order to prevent the engine from splitting the sentence unintentionally.
expect.name: split_sentences
expect.label: Split Sentences

options.label: Split on Punctuation and on Newlines

expect.help:
Sets whether the translation engine should respect the original formatting, even if it would usually correct some aspects.
The formatting aspects affected by this setting include:
- Punctuation at the beginning and end of the sentence
- Upper/lower case at the beginning of the sentence
expect.name: preserve_formatting
expect.label: Preserve Formatting

expect.help: Specify the glossary to use for the translation. Important: This requires the `source_lang` parameter to be set and the language pair of the glossary has to match the language pair of the request.
expect.name: glossary_id
expect.label: Glossary ID

expect.help: Sets which kind of tags in the text should be handled.
expect.name: tag_handling
expect.label: Tag Handling

expect.help: Comma-separated list of XML tags which never split sentences. For example `par,title`.
expect.name: non_splitting_tags
expect.label: Non Splitting Tags

expect.help: The automatic detection of the XML structure won't yield best results in all XML files. You can disable this automatic mechanism altogether by setting the `outline_detection` parameter to `false` and selecting the tags that should be considered structure tags. This will split sentences using the `splitting_tags` parameter.
expect.name: outline_detection
expect.label: Outline Detection

expect.help: Comma-separated list of XML tags which always cause splits. For example `par,title`.
expect.name: splitting_tags
expect.label: Splitting Tags

expect.help: Comma-separated list of XML tags that indicate text not to be translated. For example `par,title`.
expect.name: ignore_tags
expect.label: Ignored Tags

translateText.description: Translates a text into specified language.
